  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6994.45 sitting just below the massive 7000 strike gamma wall (17.8B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above 7000 as they hedge their long gamma exposure. The PIN regime with 123B total GEX creates a strong gravitational pull around current levels, with dealers providing natural resistance at the clustered 7000-7100 strikes above and support at the 6800 negative gamma floor below. Watch for rejection at 7000 and mean reversion back toward the 6878 flip point, as the thick positive gamma walls from 7000-7100 should cap upside momentum.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect sellers to step in hard at 7000 with choppy action likely between 6900-7000.",
